      "span_text": "In particular, if we take the representative consumer as a primitive concept of the model and impose some tractable functional form on his utility function (as done by  , for example), rather than employing a closer-to-reality approach of constructing it from the explicitly modelled group of heterogeneous consumers, then we should be well aware of any potential biases in our estimation of interest rates."
